Created files:
- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/Connection/ReconnectBackoff.cs
    Pure C# exponential backoff calculator that drives the
    ClientSessionManager retry loop (task 3.3 will compose it).
    Public API mirrors the design.md sketch:
        - ReconnectBackoff(TimeSpan initialDelay, double multiplier,
                           TimeSpan maxDelay, int maxAttempts)
        - public TimeSpan NextDelay()
        - public bool ExceededMaxAttempts { get; }
        - public void Reset()
    Two diagnostic accessors (AttemptCount, MaxAttempts) are also
    exposed so CoreIpcDiagnostics (task 5.4) can publish the live
    retry counter without re-implementing the math.

    Series semantics:
        delayMs = initialDelay * multiplier^attemptCount, then capped
        at maxDelay. Math.Pow on attemptCount keeps the formula
        explicit; NaN / +Infinity (overflow guard) collapses to
        maxDelay so degenerate parameters never produce non-finite
        TimeSpans. With the design defaults (250ms, ×2, 5s, 20) the
        emitted series is:
            250ms → 500ms → 1s → 2s → 4s → 5s × 15
        i.e. exponential growth for attempts 0..4, then the cap holds
        for the remaining 15 attempts up to the 20-call limit.

    Max-attempts contract:
        ExceededMaxAttempts becomes true once attemptCount reaches
        maxAttempts (after the maxAttempts-th NextDelay() call).
        Calling NextDelay() past that point throws
        InvalidOperationException; per design "ExceededMaxAttempts が
        true になった後は NextDelay() を呼ばず上位が
        PermanentlyDisconnected 遷移を選ぶ契約とする" the upper
        layer (ClientSessionManager) is expected to inspect the flag
        instead. Reset() clears attemptCount back to 0, restarting
        the series from initialDelay; this is what
        ClientSessionManager calls on a successful reconnect.

    Constructor validation:
        - initialDelay >= TimeSpan.Zero
        - multiplier real and >= 1.0 (rejects NaN as well to keep the
          series monotonic non-decreasing)
        - maxDelay >= initialDelay
        - maxAttempts > 0
        Each violation throws ArgumentOutOfRangeException with the
        offending value.

    Thread safety: an internal lock guards _attemptCount so the
    upcoming ClientSessionManager worker Task can safely call
    NextDelay() from a background thread while other components
    inspect ExceededMaxAttempts / AttemptCount from the main thread.

