Implementation summary:
- ReconnectBackoff lives next to ConnectionStateMachine inside the
  VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core.Connection namespace, on the existing
  VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core asmdef. It is pure C# with no Unity
  engine references, so the EditMode tests construct and drive it
  directly without any PlayerLoop dependency.
- The class is sealed and stateless apart from the attempt counter,
  so the same instance can be shared between the connect path and
  the reconnect loop in ClientSessionManager (task 3.3): success
  calls Reset(), each retry calls NextDelay(), and the manager
  switches the ConnectionStateMachine to PermanentlyDisconnected
  when ExceededMaxAttempts goes true.
- The cap math is intentionally evaluated as Math.Pow rather than
  a running multiplication so the series for attempt N is independent
  of how many earlier values were observed; this avoids floating
  point drift accumulating over the 20-attempt window.

